external_knowledge:
- "Most valuable orders" refers to the highest total order value for each customer;
- "More than one part" means the order contains more than one distinct part;
- "Exceed a total value of 100" means the total order value is greater than 100.

- 'Generous patrons' refers to customers who have spent more than $1000;
- 'Favored currency' refers to the customer's preferred currency;
- 'Completed transactions' refers to orders with a status of 'completed'.

sql:
SELECT total_amount
FROM orders
WHERE status = 'shipped' AND currency = 'USD';

external_knowledge:
- "crown jewel" refers to the top-selling or most valuable part;
- "technological giant" refers to the manufacturer, Texas Instruments;
- "sought-after" refers to the highest requested quantity in orders.

- "leading figures" refers to the top 10 customers;
- "cumulative wealth from their transactions" refers to the total order value;
- "stands tall among the crowd" means they are ranked by their total order value in descending order.

- 'Specific parts' refers to parts in category 1 with a minimum order quantity greater than 5 and a lead time less than 7 days;
- 'Completed orders' refers to orders with a status of 'completed';
- 'Preferred currency' is USD.

- "Top 3 spenders" refers to the customers with the highest total spend;
- "Noble with a generous purse" metaphorically refers to customers who spend a lot;
- "Kingdom's wealth" metaphorically refers to the total amount of money spent by customers.

- 'Net gain' refers to the profit calculated as the total revenue minus the total shipping cost.;
- 'Shines the brightest' means the highest profit margin.;
- 'Star customer' is the customer with the highest profit margin.;

- 'Shortest lead time' refers to the minimum lead time among all suppliers for a particular part;
- 'Lead time' is the duration in days from the order date to the delivery date of a part;
- 'Manufacturer part number' is a unique identifier assigned by the manufacturer for a part.

- "Highest lead times" refers to the longest time it takes for a supplier to deliver a part;
- "Stock quantity > 100" means the part must have more than 100 units in stock;
- "Supplier rank 1" means the supplier with the highest lead time within the same supplier name.

- "High revenue" refers to a total revenue greater than 1000;
- "Frequently ordered in large quantities" refers to a total quantity greater than 100;
- "Longest lead times" refers to an average lead time greater than 10 days.
